<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="72" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,381,514]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,381,406]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[276,503,381,406]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" refId="ref10795" refString="Sakai, K., Turkay, M. &amp; Aidaroos, A. A. (2015 a) One new species of a new genus, Kuwaitupogebia gen. nov., in a new family, Kuwaitupogebiidae fam. nov., from Kuwait, and two new species of the genus Upogebia from the Red Sea (Decapoda, Thalassinidea). Crustaceana, 88 (10 - 11), 1221 - 1234. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 15685403 - 00003474" type="journal article">
Sakai 
<emphasis box="[348,406,381,406]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">et al.</emphasis>
(2015a)
</bibRefCitation>
repeated their arguments to justify separating the new genus from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[1278,1388,381,406]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1278,1388,381,406]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">Upogebia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As shown below, none of the differences is real. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borradaile" authorityYear="1903" box="[666,809,417,442]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Upogebiidae</taxonomicName>
includes 11 genera (
<bibRefCitation box="[1044,1186,417,442]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" refId="ref10330" refString="Sakai, K. (2006 a) Upogebiidae of the world (Decapoda, Thalassinidea). Crustaceana Monographs, 6, 1 - 185. Available from: https: // decapoda. nhm. org / pdfs / 21981 / 21981. pdf (accessed 27 July 2017)" type="journal article">Sakai 2006a</bibRefCitation>
) but the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai, Turkay &amp; Al Aidaroos, 2015:" authorityYear="1223" box="[151,336,453,478]" class="Malacostraca" family="Kuwaitupogebiidae" genus="Kuwaitupogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,336,453,478]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">Kuwaitupogebia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1814" box="[407,517,453,478]" class="Malacostraca" family="Upogebiidae" genus="Upogebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[407,517,453,478]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">Upogebia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, rather than with any other, has been determined after examination of its 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,454,478]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">type</typeStatus>
species and comparison with similar species (see below).
</paragraph>
